handist.collections

Interface ParallelReceiver<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the objects to receive
    All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Bag, DistBag

    public interface ParallelReceiver<T>
extends Iterable<T>
    Interface representing the capability for an implementing class to receive objects of a certain type from multiple sources. The unique method should provide a clean handle to feed T objects into the implementing type, without interfering with concurrent threads using other handles to do the same.

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Removes all contents from this parallel receiver. This instance will be empty as a result.

      • contains

        boolean contains(Object v)
        Indicates if the object given as parameter is present in this instance
        Parameters:
        v - the object whose presence is to be checked
        Returns:
        true if the object is present at least once in this parallel receiver, false otherwise

      • getReceiver

        Consumer<T> getReceiver()
        Provides a new handle that will place T instances into this instance. This method may be called by multiple threads that all want to place some instances into this object. The implementation guarantees that all these threads will be able to place T instances in this object through the returned Consumer without blocking or otherwise contend for object access with other threads.
        Returns:
        a new Consumer accepting T objects

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Indicates if this parallel receiver contains any object
        Returns:
        true if this instance is empty, false otherwise

      • size

        int size()
        Returns the size (i.e.) the number of elements contained in this instance.
        Returns:
        the number of elements contained in the receiver as an integer
